 scholars and students in a number of fields, including sociology and social theory, but also to anyone interested in the intellectual life as it was lived in the mid-twentieth century, in the face of the Cold War and ideological struggle.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aSociologyxPhilosophy. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / General.2bisacsh  aEdward Shils.  aMichael Oakeshott.  aMichael Polanyi.  aSocial theory.  aTradition.  anations.  aphilosophical anthropology.  asociology.1 aAdair-Toteff, Christopher, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAdair-Toteff, Christopher, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aAltbach, Philip G., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBoyd, Richard, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEaly, Lenore T., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGrosby, Steven, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMentzel, Peter, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMullins, Phil, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNeavill, Gordon B., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPodoksik, Efraim, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPooley, Jefferson, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSchneider, Thomas, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSchnusenberg, Christine C., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTurner, Bryan S., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTurner, Stephen P., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTurner, Stephen, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.g